EDUCATION MAY SUBSTITUTE FOR SPECIALIZED EXPERIENCE AS FOLLOWS:
GS-09:
-You have successfully completed master's or equivalent graduate degree or;
-You have successfully completed 2 full years of progressively higher level graduate education leading to such a degree or;
-You have successfully completed a LL.B. or J.D., if related or;
-You have a combination of experience and education as described above that equates to one year of experience. Such education must demonstrate the knowledge, skills, and abilities necessary to do the work of the position. Education completed in foreign colleges or universities may be used to meet the qualification requirements if the applicant can provide documentation indicating that the foreign education is comparable to that received in an accredited educational institution in the United States. It is the responsibility of the applicant to provide such evidence when applying for further information, visit: http://www.ed.gov/about/offices/list/ous/international/usnei/us/edlite-visitus-forrecog.html.See the Office of Personnel Management's General Policies for information on crediting education.

MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
GS-09:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-07 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: 1) Preparing technical documentation and data to establish criteria and estimates for ALRE repair, maintenance, overhaul and installation;
2) Developing Computer Numerical Control programs, running system tests and modifying CNC equipment as necessary to maintain system and program efficiency;
3) Anticipating testing problems and investigating their possible causes in order to recommend solutions and avoid unnecessary delays;
4) Generating fabrication plans to include essential equipment, material and labor needs to ensure all project requirements are met within scheduling and budgetary limits. GS-07:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-05 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: 1) Providing technical/advisory services in support of the manufacturing, repairing, and overhauling of various ALRE and SE components and systems;
2) Programing and operating various CNC machines as well as a large variety of conventional machines;
3) Engaging in the design and fabrication of ALRE and/or associated testing components/assemblies
4) Furnishing technical information, assisting and advising on the integration of technical diverse complex systems. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.

Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-05 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector assisting in the analysis or evaluation of improvements in policies, plans, methods, procedures, systems, or techniques of a supply program or process. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following: 1.) Preparing correspondence on program issues and incorrect requisitions;
